WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:03.958
A dollar eighty-nine.
Why is this $1.89?

2
00:00:04.120 --> 00:00:06.076
Why is there no
haggling in this country?

3
00:00:06.240 --> 00:00:09.232
We like to think we've progressed
beyond a knife fight for a drink.

4
00:00:09.400 --> 00:00:11.994
Not me.
Everything should be negotiable.

5
00:00:12.160 --> 00:00:14.037
- Restaurants too?
- Absolutely.

6
00:00:14.200 --> 00:00:17.078
Are you telling me there is
no room to move on pasta?

7
00:00:17.240 --> 00:00:19.037
All starches are a scam.

8
00:00:19.480 --> 00:00:21.596
Yeah. especially ziti.
with that big hole.

9
00:00:23.040 --> 00:00:24.393
Excuse me. How much is this?

10
00:00:24.560 --> 00:00:26.676
- A dollar nineteen.
- I'll give you a quarter.

11
00:00:26.840 --> 00:00:28.319
Get the hell out of here.

12
00:00:28.480 --> 00:00:30.948
- Tell him 40 and no fork.
- Thirty.

13
00:00:31.120 --> 00:00:33.350
That's it. You leave
and never come back.

14
00:00:33.520 --> 00:00:35.590
How about we leave
and come back in a week?

15
00:00:35.760 --> 00:00:37.034
Deal.

16
00:00:37.760 --> 00:00:40.558
All right. See?
We got something there.

17
00:00:44.840 --> 00:00:46.114
Oh. check it out.

18
00:00:46.680 --> 00:00:49.274
Kenny Rogers Roasters
finally opened.

19
00:00:49.440 --> 00:00:52.750
Hey. look at the size of
that neon chicken on the roof.

20
00:00:52.920 --> 00:00:54.558
Rogers can't sell chicken around here.

21
00:00:54.720 --> 00:00:56.392
We got chicken places
on every block.

22
00:00:56.560 --> 00:00:58.676
He is The Gambler.

23
00:00:59.120 --> 00:01:02.999
Well. I gotta meet Newman at the pet
store. I'm helping him pick out a turtle.

24
00:01:03.200 --> 00:01:05.919
- Try and stay calm.
- Yeah. yeah. yeah.

25
00:01:07.000 --> 00:01:08.797
- Hey. Jerry?
- Seth.

26
00:01:08.960 --> 00:01:11.030
Wow. what has it been.
like. five years?

27
00:01:11.200 --> 00:01:13.111
- At least.
- You want to grab lunch?

28
00:01:13.600 --> 00:01:15.352
I'm actually
headed back to the office.

29
00:01:15.520 --> 00:01:17.033
Seth. it's me.

30
00:01:17.200 --> 00:01:19.998
What's more important than catching
up with an old college buddy?

31
00:01:20.160 --> 00:01:22.549
Well. I am supposed
to be in this meeting.

32
00:01:22.720 --> 00:01:27.271
Blow it off. Remember Poli-Sci?
How many of those did we go to?

33
00:01:27.800 --> 00:01:30.712
- All right. I guess I can go.
- All right. All right.

34
00:01:30.880 --> 00:01:32.916
- Hey. whatever happened to Moochy?
- He's dead.

35
00:01:33.080 --> 00:01:34.513
Is that right?

36
00:01:35.040 --> 00:01:37.918
Still don't know how you can call lunch
with me a business expense.

37
00:01:38.080 --> 00:01:39.991
- What do you think of the catalogue?
- Stinks.

38
00:01:40.160 --> 00:01:41.673
There. we just talked business.

39
00:01:42.960 --> 00:01:45.269
We have the down comforter
and the cookware you liked.

40
00:01:45.440 --> 00:01:48.000
Great. Put it on the Peterman
account with the other stuff.

41
00:01:48.160 --> 00:01:49.752
You know what we have
you might like?

42
00:01:49.920 --> 00:01:51.638
I'll take it.

43
00:01:51.800 --> 00:01:54.075
Hey. you like?

44
00:01:55.680 --> 00:01:57.591
I think it looks very nice on you.

45
00:01:58.360 --> 00:01:59.998
Really?

46
00:02:01.560 --> 00:02:03.198
Elaine?

47
00:02:03.760 --> 00:02:05.910
- The Peterman account?
- Why not?

48
00:02:06.080 --> 00:02:08.640
And some hair
for my little friend here.

49
00:02:09.480 --> 00:02:11.072
So how's your stand-up career?

50
00:02:11.240 --> 00:02:13.879
Good. As a matter of fact.
I almost had my own show in Japan.

51
00:02:14.040 --> 00:02:15.792
- You speak Japanese?
- No.

52
00:02:15.960 --> 00:02:19.032
So you would have done it in
Japan. but in English?

53
00:02:20.840 --> 00:02:22.671
I don't know.

54
00:02:24.600 --> 00:02:25.919
So. what's this job of yours?

55
00:02:26.400 --> 00:02:30.075
Big investment firm.
We just got the Citibank account.

56
00:02:30.240 --> 00:02:33.232
In fact. today was our
first big meeting with them.

57
00:02:34.160 --> 00:02:35.957
The meeting you blew off?

58
00:02:36.120 --> 00:02:37.917
Yeah.

59
00:02:39.200 --> 00:02:41.316
Wasn't that kind of important?

60
00:02:42.880 --> 00:02:44.552
Yeah.

61
00:02:46.960 --> 00:02:50.236
And I bought a whole new set
of cookware and a water pick.

62
00:02:50.400 --> 00:02:52.834
- You use a water pick?
- Sure. Water pick...

63
00:02:53.000 --> 00:02:55.116
...floss. Plax. brush. Listerine.

64
00:02:55.280 --> 00:02:57.748
So you go into the bathroom 11.
you're in bed by what. 2?

65
00:02:57.920 --> 00:03:01.708
At the latest. Oh. hang on a second.
I've got another call.

66
00:03:02.800 --> 00:03:04.552
- Hello?
- Good day. Miss Benes...

67
00:03:04.720 --> 00:03:06.073
...it's Roger lpswich.

68
00:03:06.240 --> 00:03:08.276
Oh. hey. how are things
doing in accounting?

69
00:03:08.440 --> 00:03:11.512
Miss Benes. I notice you've been
charging quite a bit of merchandise...

70
00:03:11.680 --> 00:03:12.999
...on the Peterman account.

71
00:03:13.160 --> 00:03:15.355
Well. I am the president.

72
00:03:15.520 --> 00:03:19.229
Yes. and we're all very impressed.

73
00:03:19.400 --> 00:03:23.393
Nevertheless. the expense account
is for business purposes only.

74
00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:28.039
Well... Well. isn't the president
allowed to do anything that they want?

75
00:03:28.200 --> 00:03:29.713
No.

76
00:03:30.720 --> 00:03:34.872
I'll be in your office
first thing tomorrow. Good day.

77
00:03:35.040 --> 00:03:36.951
Good day.

78
00:03:42.600 --> 00:03:44.238
Hello?

79
00:03:45.800 --> 00:03:47.631
Anybody?

80
00:03:52.800 --> 00:03:54.074
Hey.

81
00:03:54.240 --> 00:03:57.915
Hey. Why didn't you
get the big one?

82
00:03:58.760 --> 00:04:01.399
This hat just bottles in the heat.
I don't even need a coat.

83
00:04:01.560 --> 00:04:02.879
It's unbelievable.

84
00:04:03.040 --> 00:04:05.918
- I don't believe it.
- And I got a date with the saleswoman.

85
00:04:06.240 --> 00:04:08.708
She got a little Marisa Tomei
thing going on.

86
00:04:08.880 --> 00:04:12.077
Too bad you've got a little
George Costanza thing going on.

87
00:04:12.240 --> 00:04:14.708
I'm going out with her tomorrow.
She had errands to run.

88
00:04:14.880 --> 00:04:16.313
That's a date?

89
00:04:16.480 --> 00:04:18.835
What's the difference?
You know the way I work.

90
00:04:19.000 --> 00:04:20.638
I'm like a commercial jingle.

91
00:04:20.800 --> 00:04:24.634
First. it's a little irritating. You hear it
a few times. You hum it in the shower.

92
00:04:24.800 --> 00:04:27.997
By the third date. it's "By Mennen."

93
00:04:28.960 --> 00:04:30.871
How you make sure
you get to the third date?

94
00:04:31.040 --> 00:04:33.918
If there's any doubt.
I do a leave-behind.

95
00:04:34.080 --> 00:04:37.550
Keys. gloves. scarf.
I go back to her place to pick it up...

96
00:04:37.720 --> 00:04:40.314
...date number two.
- That is so old.

97
00:04:40.480 --> 00:04:42.994
Why don't you just show up
at her house in a wooden horse?

98
00:04:46.360 --> 00:04:48.078
By Mennen

99
00:04:49.120 --> 00:04:50.712
What the...?

100
00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:58.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

101
00:05:02.400 --> 00:05:03.674
What's going on in there?

102
00:05:03.840 --> 00:05:05.751
- What?
- That light.

103
00:05:05.920 --> 00:05:07.592
Oh. the red.

104
00:05:07.760 --> 00:05:11.673
Yeah. it's the chicken roaster sign.
It's right across from my window.

105
00:05:11.840 --> 00:05:13.193
Can't you shut the shades?

106
00:05:13.360 --> 00:05:15.351
They are shut.

107
00:05:15.520 --> 00:05:17.397
By the way. your friend Seth.
he stopped by.

108
00:05:17.560 --> 00:05:19.516
- Yeah? What'd he have to say?
- He was fired.

109
00:05:22.080 --> 00:05:24.469
As you can see. the comforter
I expensed is actually...

110
00:05:24.640 --> 00:05:27.791
...the Aristotle goose down tunic.

111
00:05:28.200 --> 00:05:31.078
- What do you think?
- Another bull's-eye.

112
00:05:31.240 --> 00:05:33.754
Well. Mr. Ipswich.
since every one of my expenses...

113
00:05:33.920 --> 00:05:38.550
...was obviously
for a legitimate business purpose...

114
00:05:38.720 --> 00:05:41.757
I just need to see the
sable hat you purchased yesterday.

115
00:05:41.920 --> 00:05:43.956
The hat? Why do you need to
see the hat?

116
00:05:44.120 --> 00:05:46.031
It cost $8000.

117
00:05:46.200 --> 00:05:47.679
What?

118
00:05:51.440 --> 00:05:54.830
Seth. if you knew the meeting was so
important. why did you go to lunch?

119
00:05:55.000 --> 00:05:56.319
We're old college buddies.

120
00:05:56.480 --> 00:05:58.471
I only knew you through Moochy.

121
00:05:59.160 --> 00:06:01.230
Hey. Jerry. don't worry about it.
all right?

122
00:06:01.400 --> 00:06:04.597
The important thing is.
is we got a chance to catch up.

123
00:06:04.760 --> 00:06:07.274
Mind if I grab the want ads?

124
00:06:07.680 --> 00:06:10.353
Actually. I haven't read
Tank McNamara yet.

125
00:06:15.920 --> 00:06:18.229
How's life on the red planet?

126
00:06:19.360 --> 00:06:22.511
It's killing me.
I can't eat. I can't sleep.

127
00:06:22.680 --> 00:06:26.832
All I can see is that giant red sun
in the shape of a chicken.

128
00:06:27.360 --> 00:06:29.749
Well. did you go down to the
Kenny Rogers and complain?

129
00:06:29.920 --> 00:06:31.512
Oh. they gave me the heave-ho.

130
00:06:31.920 --> 00:06:35.833
I don't think that Kenny Rogers has
any idea what's going on down there.

131
00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:37.592
What are you doing?

132
00:06:39.280 --> 00:06:41.748
- Getting some cereal.
- That's tomato juice.

133
00:06:46.400 --> 00:06:48.152
That looked like milk to me.

134
00:06:50.280 --> 00:06:53.397
Jerry. my rods
and cones are all screwed up.

135
00:06:53.840 --> 00:06:55.432
All right. that's it.

136
00:06:55.600 --> 00:06:57.830
I gotta move in with you. Jerry.

137
00:07:00.160 --> 00:07:02.071
I don't know. Kramer.

138
00:07:02.440 --> 00:07:05.113
My concern is that...

139
00:07:05.280 --> 00:07:08.238
...living together after a while we...

140
00:07:09.320 --> 00:07:12.790
...might start to get on
each other's nerves a little.

141
00:07:13.600 --> 00:07:15.875
Listen. I got an idea.
You're a heavy sleeper. right?

142
00:07:16.040 --> 00:07:17.393
Why don't we switch apartments?

143
00:07:17.560 --> 00:07:19.676
Or I could sleep in the park.

144
00:07:20.640 --> 00:07:24.474
You can knock these walls down.
make it an eight-room luxury suite.

145
00:07:24.640 --> 00:07:29.111
Jerry. these are load bearing walls.
They're not gonna come down.

146
00:07:29.720 --> 00:07:31.438
Yeah. that's no good.

147
00:07:31.600 --> 00:07:33.750
I may have to drive that place
out of business.

148
00:07:33.920 --> 00:07:36.912
- Well. how are you going to do that?
- Like we did in the '60s.

149
00:07:37.080 --> 00:07:39.071
Taking it to the streets.

150
00:07:44.480 --> 00:07:48.393
- Thanks. George. but I got it from here.
- Oh. no. I'm in already. Come on.

151
00:07:50.240 --> 00:07:53.277
So you wanna
get together tomorrow?

152
00:07:53.440 --> 00:07:55.351
No. I'm gonna be pretty busy.

153
00:07:55.880 --> 00:07:59.759
- What about this weekend?
- I'm gonna be busy for a while.

154
00:08:00.080 --> 00:08:02.640
Okay. See you.

155
00:08:02.800 --> 00:08:05.360
Hey. you forgot your keys.

156
00:08:05.520 --> 00:08:08.159
- Those aren't my keys.
- Well. they're not mine.

157
00:08:12.000 --> 00:08:15.310
They are my keys. How weird.

158
00:08:16.080 --> 00:08:18.389
- Goodbye. George.
- Yeah. bye.

159
00:08:19.400 --> 00:08:20.913
George. bye.

160
00:08:23.080 --> 00:08:27.710
Hello? You are not gonna
believe the date I just had.

161
00:08:29.080 --> 00:08:31.514
Costanza

162
00:08:33.560 --> 00:08:35.357
What do you mean.
you don't have the hat?

163
00:08:35.520 --> 00:08:37.272
I left it at Heather's. Are these alive?

164
00:08:37.440 --> 00:08:39.431
No. dead.

165
00:08:39.960 --> 00:08:42.155
George. I need
that Russian hat back.

166
00:08:42.320 --> 00:08:44.231
All right. all right. I'll call Heather.

167
00:08:44.400 --> 00:08:47.597
You'll get your hat back.
I will get a second date.

168
00:08:47.760 --> 00:08:50.399
Now. watch the magic.

169
00:08:52.280 --> 00:08:54.236
Dial nine. Merlin.

170
00:08:58.840 --> 00:09:02.515
- Hello?
- Heather. hi. it's George Costanza.

171
00:09:04.000 --> 00:09:06.719
Listen. I don't mean
to bother you. but silly me...

172
00:09:06.880 --> 00:09:10.236
...l... I think I may have left my hat
in your apartment. so I thought...

173
00:09:10.400 --> 00:09:13.710
...l'd just come by later and pick it up.
- You didn't leave a hat here.

174
00:09:13.880 --> 00:09:18.795
I'm pretty sure I left it behind the
cushion of the chair. accidentally.

175
00:09:18.960 --> 00:09:20.996
No hat. George. I've gotta go.

176
00:09:21.160 --> 00:09:24.755
You know what.
maybe I'll just come... Hey. hey.

177
00:09:30.400 --> 00:09:34.234
- Seth?
- Jerry. hi. What do you think?

178
00:09:34.400 --> 00:09:37.039
I think you're taking the trash
out for this chicken place...

179
00:09:37.200 --> 00:09:40.556
...but that couldn't be.
- Yeah. I'm the new manager.

180
00:09:40.720 --> 00:09:43.359
But you were an executive.
This is fast food.

181
00:09:43.520 --> 00:09:45.909
Not fast food. Good food quickly.

182
00:09:46.080 --> 00:09:48.389
Hey. next time lunch
will be on me. huh. Jer?

183
00:09:48.560 --> 00:09:49.913
Hey!

184
00:09:50.280 --> 00:09:53.078
Stay away from the chicken!
It's bad!

185
00:09:53.240 --> 00:09:55.754
Bad chicken! Mess you up!

186
00:09:55.920 --> 00:09:58.480
That's not going to be
good for business.

187
00:09:58.640 --> 00:10:01.029
That's not gonna be
good for anybody.

188
00:10:06.640 --> 00:10:09.393
I'm so glad we switched apartments.
It was the perfect solution.

189
00:10:09.560 --> 00:10:13.599
Kramer. if I'm gonna live over there.
you gotta take some of this stuff out.

190
00:10:13.760 --> 00:10:16.274
I mean. this thing
is really freaking me out.

191
00:10:16.440 --> 00:10:19.830
I feel like it's gonna come to life
in the middle of the night and kill me.

192
00:10:20.120 --> 00:10:22.554
What. Mr. Marbles? He's harmless.

193
00:10:22.720 --> 00:10:26.998
And one other thing. I don't want
Newman using my...

194
00:10:27.160 --> 00:10:28.718
Oh. no.

195
00:10:29.160 --> 00:10:30.878
- Nice place you got here. Kramer.
- Yeah.

196
00:10:31.040 --> 00:10:34.237
A man could really
get some thinking done.

197
00:10:36.320 --> 00:10:38.959
Don't get too comfortable.
As soon as Seth gets a real job...

198
00:10:39.120 --> 00:10:42.078
...you two are going back in that
chicken supernova.

199
00:10:43.360 --> 00:10:46.238
What's that. Rogers chicken?
Oh. get that out of here.

200
00:10:46.400 --> 00:10:49.278
I don't know. The man makes
a pretty strong bird.

201
00:10:49.440 --> 00:10:51.351
Yeah. but I'm boycotting.

202
00:11:05.120 --> 00:11:06.712
- What is that. hickory?
- Yeah.

203
00:11:07.120 --> 00:11:09.270
It's the wood that makes it good.

204
00:11:10.080 --> 00:11:11.513
Really?

205
00:11:12.280 --> 00:11:15.511
Stop it. What's the matter with you?

206
00:11:21.600 --> 00:11:23.750
- Can I help you?
- Hi. yeah. I'm Elaine Benes.

207
00:11:23.920 --> 00:11:28.357
We met at Barney's.
I'm a friend of George Costanza's.

208
00:11:28.560 --> 00:11:30.039
Hi.

209
00:11:30.200 --> 00:11:34.239
Whether you're aware of it or not.
George had this pathetic little plan...

210
00:11:34.400 --> 00:11:38.552
...to leave something behind so he
could try and weasel a second date.

211
00:11:38.720 --> 00:11:40.312
- Really?
- I know.

212
00:11:40.480 --> 00:11:42.516
He... He has a real
confidence problem.

213
00:11:42.680 --> 00:11:44.830
- Well. not really...
- George.

214
00:11:46.960 --> 00:11:49.190
I know you told him
that you didn't have the hat...

215
00:11:49.360 --> 00:11:53.069
...because you didn't want to see
him again. and more sympathetic...

216
00:11:53.240 --> 00:11:54.992
...I could not be...

217
00:11:56.120 --> 00:11:59.032
...but I really do need
to have the hat back.

218
00:11:59.200 --> 00:12:01.839
Look. I don't know what to tell you.
but there's no hat here.

219
00:12:02.000 --> 00:12:04.639
I mean. maybe the maid took it.
I had people over but...

220
00:12:04.800 --> 00:12:05.949
Well. that makes sense.

221
00:12:06.120 --> 00:12:09.078
Well. then you wouldn't mind
if we took a second look around?

222
00:12:09.520 --> 00:12:10.999
Be my guest.

223
00:12:11.160 --> 00:12:12.832
Good to see you again.

224
00:12:17.680 --> 00:12:20.911
She's bluffing. She's got it
stashed away in there somewhere.

225
00:12:21.080 --> 00:12:23.878
This is an absolute disaster.

226
00:12:24.040 --> 00:12:26.793
Oh. I don't know. Check this out.

227
00:12:32.320 --> 00:12:34.595
You stole her clock?

228
00:12:38.240 --> 00:12:39.958
Well done.

229
00:12:40.320 --> 00:12:43.676
Yep. This is one for our side.

230
00:13:01.320 --> 00:13:03.197
What is that creaking?

231
00:13:03.360 --> 00:13:06.079
It's lik e I'm in the hold of a ship.

232
00:13:06.240 --> 00:13:08.196
I've gotta relax.

233
00:13:13.720 --> 00:13:15.278
Hello?

234
00:13:16.120 --> 00:13:18.634
Is somebody there?

235
00:13:18.800 --> 00:13:20.950
Mr. Marbles?

236
00:13:23.920 --> 00:13:26.992
So I told lpswich I'd have
the hat by this afternoon.

237
00:13:27.160 --> 00:13:30.550
- What am I going to do?
- You should sleep with him.

238
00:13:36.320 --> 00:13:37.912
Hi. buddy.

239
00:13:38.960 --> 00:13:41.428
I'm on no sleep. no sleep.

240
00:13:41.600 --> 00:13:44.558
You don't know what it's like.
Things are creaking and cracking...

241
00:13:44.720 --> 00:13:47.314
...and that red light
is burning my brain.

242
00:13:48.000 --> 00:13:51.197
- You look a little stressed.
- Oh. I'm stressed.

243
00:13:54.720 --> 00:13:58.190
So. Kramer. what am I supposed to do?
If I don't have that fur hat by 4:00...

244
00:13:58.360 --> 00:14:00.555
...they're gonna take me down
like Nixon.

245
00:14:00.720 --> 00:14:03.188
You know my friend
Bob Sacamano?

246
00:14:03.360 --> 00:14:04.793
I thought he was Kramer's friend.

247
00:14:04.960 --> 00:14:07.520
He called last night about
3 a.m. and we got to talking.

248
00:14:07.680 --> 00:14:11.309
He sells Russian hats
down at Battery Park. 40 bucks.

249
00:14:12.000 --> 00:14:14.150
Forty bucks? Are they sable?

250
00:14:14.320 --> 00:14:16.470
No. but the difference is negligible.

251
00:14:17.600 --> 00:14:20.034
Oh. yeah. I like this idea.

252
00:14:20.800 --> 00:14:23.872
- All right. Let's give it a shot. Let's go.
- Giddyup.

253
00:14:26.720 --> 00:14:29.712
- It's getting cold. It's getting cold.
- That was a close one.

254
00:14:29.920 --> 00:14:31.319
Why do we keep this from Jerry?

255
00:14:31.520 --> 00:14:35.991
If Jerry finds out I'm hooked on Rogers
chicken. I'm back with the red menace.

256
00:14:38.240 --> 00:14:41.038
Miss Benes. the hat you charged
to the company was sable.

257
00:14:41.600 --> 00:14:43.830
This is nutria.

258
00:14:45.000 --> 00:14:49.516
Well. that's a... It's a kind of sable.

259
00:14:49.800 --> 00:14:53.031
No. it's a kind of rat.

260
00:14:54.240 --> 00:14:56.196
That's a rat hat?

261
00:14:56.440 --> 00:14:59.955
And a poorly made one.
even by rat hat standards.

262
00:15:01.320 --> 00:15:03.595
I've no choice but to
recommended your termination...

263
00:15:03.760 --> 00:15:06.433
...to the board of directors.
Nothing short of the approval...

264
00:15:06.600 --> 00:15:08.875
...of Peterman himself
will save you this time.

265
00:15:09.040 --> 00:15:11.474
But... But he's in the Burmese jungle.

266
00:15:11.840 --> 00:15:13.751
And quite mad. too. from what I hear.

267
00:15:14.400 --> 00:15:17.597
Wait a minute.
Wait a minute. Can I fire you?

268
00:15:18.240 --> 00:15:20.037
No.

269
00:15:22.160 --> 00:15:24.151
- So Heather called?
- Yeah. but get this.

270
00:15:24.320 --> 00:15:28.029
The message said.
"Call me if you have the time."

271
00:15:28.200 --> 00:15:30.873
If I have the time? You got it?

272
00:15:31.040 --> 00:15:33.918
No. but this is all very exciting.

273
00:15:34.400 --> 00:15:36.311
She knows that I have her clock.

274
00:15:36.480 --> 00:15:38.311
I know that she has my hat.

275
00:15:38.480 --> 00:15:40.630
I think she's getting ready
to make an exchange.

276
00:15:40.800 --> 00:15:44.475
Well. there is the possibility that
you've gone right out of your mind.

277
00:15:46.080 --> 00:15:48.640
I've looked at that. It seems unlikely.

278
00:15:48.800 --> 00:15:50.597
Well. I'd look again.

279
00:15:50.760 --> 00:15:53.115
So how come you didn't call
Jerry about all this?

280
00:15:53.280 --> 00:15:55.510
Jerry. I can't talk to Jerry anymore.

281
00:15:55.680 --> 00:15:58.717
Ever since he moved into
that apartment he's too much...

282
00:15:58.880 --> 00:16:00.632
...like you.

283
00:16:00.800 --> 00:16:02.631
That's a shame.

284
00:16:04.960 --> 00:16:07.633
Seth. you're the manager.
Can't you turn off that sign?

285
00:16:07.800 --> 00:16:11.270
Jerry. I lied.
I'm just an assistant manager.

286
00:16:12.240 --> 00:16:15.596
Number 67. family feast.

287
00:16:15.760 --> 00:16:18.752
Number 67. Right here. Right here.

288
00:16:18.920 --> 00:16:21.593
- Hello. Newman.
- Hello. Jerry.

289
00:16:21.760 --> 00:16:23.751
And don't forget
your steamed broccoli.

290
00:16:23.920 --> 00:16:25.194
Hold it.

291
00:16:25.760 --> 00:16:28.320
Broccoli? Newman.
you wouldn't eat broccoli...

292
00:16:28.480 --> 00:16:31.199
...if it was deep fried
in chocolate sauce.

293
00:16:32.640 --> 00:16:37.191
I love broccoli. It's good for you.

294
00:16:37.360 --> 00:16:38.952
Really?

295
00:16:39.360 --> 00:16:41.999
Then maybe
you'd like to have a piece.

296
00:16:42.600 --> 00:16:44.431
Gladly.

297
00:16:50.000 --> 00:16:51.991
Vile weed!

298
00:16:52.720 --> 00:16:54.312
It's for Kramer. isn't it? I knew it.

299
00:16:54.480 --> 00:16:56.550
The greasy doorknob.
The licking of the fingers.

300
00:16:56.720 --> 00:16:59.757
- He's hooked on the chicken. isn't he?
- Yes! Yes. now. please...

301
00:16:59.920 --> 00:17:01.672
...someone. honey mustard.

302
00:17:14.440 --> 00:17:17.910
Newman. what took you...
Hey. buddy.

303
00:17:18.080 --> 00:17:19.638
- That was good.
- Expecting Newman?

304
00:17:19.800 --> 00:17:21.711
That's funny. because
I happened upon him...

305
00:17:21.880 --> 00:17:23.552
...down at the
Kenny Rogers Roasters.

306
00:17:23.720 --> 00:17:26.553
Kenny Rogers.
Oh. boy. I hate that place.

307
00:17:26.720 --> 00:17:29.678
He was buying quite a load of chicken.
almost enough for two people.

308
00:17:29.840 --> 00:17:32.115
- As long as one of them is not him.
- Yeah.

309
00:17:32.280 --> 00:17:34.874
Oh. hey. you know.
Elaine. she stopped by.

310
00:17:35.040 --> 00:17:37.474
Yeah. dropped off
that Bob Sacamano hat.

311
00:17:37.640 --> 00:17:40.473
Yeah. oh. she's upset with him.
Yes. sirree.

312
00:17:40.640 --> 00:17:42.790
Yeah. well. thanks for stopping by.

313
00:17:43.200 --> 00:17:45.634
I sure do miss my apartment.

314
00:17:45.800 --> 00:17:47.756
Maybe I'll switch back.

315
00:17:47.920 --> 00:17:49.638
You don't want to think about that.

316
00:17:49.800 --> 00:17:52.553
Otherwise. I'd have no choice
but to put that banner back up...

317
00:17:52.720 --> 00:17:55.837
...and run that Rogers
right out of town.

318
00:17:56.000 --> 00:18:00.118
I don't think you will. Matter of fact I'll
save you the trouble. I'll do it myself.

319
00:18:00.280 --> 00:18:02.430
Go ahead. Put the banner up.
Doesn't matter to me.

320
00:18:02.600 --> 00:18:04.318
- All right.
- No. Jerry.

321
00:18:04.480 --> 00:18:06.550
I need that chicken!
I've got to have that ch...

322
00:18:06.720 --> 00:18:10.349
Now. you leave those roasters alone!
Kenny never hurt anybody!

323
00:18:11.280 --> 00:18:14.078
- You got a little problem.
- Oh. I got a big problem. Jerry!

324
00:18:26.120 --> 00:18:27.997
Here. Kneel here.

325
00:18:28.160 --> 00:18:29.309
- What?
- Kneel.

326
00:18:29.480 --> 00:18:31.471
Kneel? Okay.

327
00:18:34.080 --> 00:18:35.672
Elaine.

328
00:18:39.320 --> 00:18:40.719
Mr. Peterman.

329
00:18:48.480 --> 00:18:49.833
You speak Burmese?

330
00:18:50.000 --> 00:18:52.594
No. Elaine. that was gibberish.

331
00:18:54.880 --> 00:18:57.713
So did you have any
trouble finding the place?

332
00:18:57.880 --> 00:18:59.871
No. you're the only...

333
00:19:00.480 --> 00:19:03.995
...white-poet-warlord
in the neighbourhood.

334
00:19:05.720 --> 00:19:07.312
Are you an assassin?

335
00:19:07.480 --> 00:19:10.233
I work for your mail order catalogue.

336
00:19:10.400 --> 00:19:15.428
You're an errand girl sent
by grocery clerks to collect a bill.

337
00:19:15.600 --> 00:19:19.673
Well. actually. I do have a bill here.

338
00:19:19.840 --> 00:19:23.674
If you could just sign this
expense form...

339
00:19:23.840 --> 00:19:26.479
...I think I could still make
the last fan boat out of here.

340
00:19:27.200 --> 00:19:29.270
I'd be happy to. Elaine.

341
00:19:29.440 --> 00:19:30.953
Here you go.

342
00:19:32.040 --> 00:19:34.508
But I will have to see this hat.

343
00:19:36.480 --> 00:19:37.993
Right.

344
00:19:46.160 --> 00:19:47.479
So how do you want to do this?

345
00:19:47.640 --> 00:19:50.598
All right. George. I'll be honest.

346
00:19:50.760 --> 00:19:53.399
The first time we went out.
I found you very irritating.

347
00:19:53.560 --> 00:19:55.596
But after seeing you
a couple of times...

348
00:19:56.000 --> 00:19:58.719
...you sort of got stuck in my head.

349
00:19:58.880 --> 00:20:00.598
Costanza

350
00:20:02.080 --> 00:20:04.150
So you really don't have my hat?

351
00:20:04.320 --> 00:20:06.072
What?

352
00:20:10.080 --> 00:20:11.354
Let's go do something.

353
00:20:11.520 --> 00:20:15.308
- What's in the bag?
- Oh. that's... That's a sandwich.

354
00:20:18.560 --> 00:20:19.788
Damn salami.

355
00:20:21.800 --> 00:20:23.631
My clock.

356
00:20:24.320 --> 00:20:26.595
- You stole it?
- That damn delicatessen.

357
00:20:26.760 --> 00:20:29.911
That is the last time they
screw up one of my orders.

358
00:20:35.680 --> 00:20:39.116
Hey. Seth. Man. it is coming
down hard out there.

359
00:20:41.960 --> 00:20:43.678
Oh. gross.

360
00:20:45.280 --> 00:20:47.157
That's not gonna be
good for business.

361
00:20:47.320 --> 00:20:49.754
That's not gonna be
good for anybody.

362
00:20:58.960 --> 00:21:00.473
Kenny?

363
00:21:03.400 --> 00:21:05.038
Kenny?

364
00:21:14.840 --> 00:21:16.114
Kenny.

365
00:21:16.520 --> 00:21:18.078
Kenny.

366
00:21:21.440 --> 00:21:22.998
Kenny.

367
00:21:23.520 --> 00:21:25.112
Home at last.

368
00:21:31.240 --> 00:21:32.559
Is someone there?

369
00:21:35.680 --> 00:21:37.557
Mr. Marbles.

370
00:21:38.400 --> 00:21:40.356
This is the urban sombrero.

371
00:21:40.520 --> 00:21:42.829
I put it on the last catalogue cover.

372
00:21:48.600 --> 00:21:50.556
The horror.

373
00:21:51.640 --> 00:21:53.596
The horror.

374
00:21:54.305 --> 00:22:54.604
